                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1CANTMF"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed at ISAC facility",
                "at TRIUMF using DRAGON separator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Differentially pumped windowless gas target with",
                "effective length of 12.3 cm filled with H2 at the",
                "pressure of 5.76+-0.14 torr. Incoming beam with energy",
                "of 518.6 keV/A entered the gass target.Outgoing energy",
                "was measured to be 499.6 keV/A."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Recoil ions were momentum analysed in DRAGON",
                "two stage electromagnetic separator, each  consisting",
                "of with one magnetic and one electrostatic dipole.",
                "Only one charge state can be transported through the",
                "length of DRAGON separator. Ions are identified in",
                "focal plane detector of the spectrometer, which consist",
                "of several detectors."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BGO"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Prompt and de-excitation gamma-rays emitted",
                "from the gas target were detected using array of 30",
                "closely packed BGO hexagonal crystals with solid",
                "angle coverage of 90% from the center of the target."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MCPLT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Ion velocity was measured using two",
                "micro-channel plate detectors separated by 57 cm."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " For ion identification a hybrid",
                "telescope detector consisting of a double sided",
                "silicon strip detector and ionization chamber"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Inverse kinematics was used in the",
                "experiment. For identification of recoil ions, time",
                "of flight (TOF) as well as dE-E method was used.",
                "Local TOF of focal plane detector as well as        C26",
                "between BGO detector and focal plane detector were",
                "used for ion identification"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Heavy ion beam of 34S was produced by the DRAGON",
                "off-line ion source."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
            {
